1
00:00:45,005 --> 00:00:47,855
Could you close the door,
or the membrane will come in

2
00:00:48,004 --> 00:00:50,334
and the humidity in the mike
will be ruined.

3
00:00:50,484 --> 00:00:53,476
But I'll die in the steam
if you lock me in the washroom!

4
00:00:54,003 --> 00:00:54,992
Go on, close it.

5
00:00:56,483 --> 00:00:59,474
Good morning to you, blockmates.

6
00:01:00,522 --> 00:01:02,990
I wish you a fruitful working day

7
00:01:04,002 --> 00:01:05,992
on this pleasant summer morning.

8
00:01:06,521 --> 00:01:11,514
Today is August 28, 1962.
Nothing but sunshine.

9
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:14,720
The temperature is normal
for the season.

10
00:01:16,519 --> 00:01:18,334
Announcement for this Saturday...

11
00:01:18,519 --> 00:01:20,169
For the workers' entertainment

12
00:01:20,999 --> 00:01:26,516
The National Defence Alliance
will be holding their Flying Day.

13
00:01:27,518 --> 00:01:31,510
I expect a large turnout
from all blockmates.

14
00:01:33,996 --> 00:01:35,987
To hell with these damn razors.

15
00:01:38,516 --> 00:01:40,983
Here is an announcement.

16
00:01:41,515 --> 00:01:45,985
The Politburo of the League of
Communist Youth

17
00:01:46,994 --> 00:01:48,507
is running a competition

18
00:01:48,994 --> 00:01:50,984
for those under the age of thirty.

19
00:01:51,673 --> 00:01:54,665
Who knows what,
what do I know... who knows?

20
00:01:55,673 --> 00:01:56,882
Go for it, youngsters!

21
00:01:57,672 --> 00:02:00,140
The situation of the winners...

22
00:02:00,672 --> 00:02:03,139
To travel to and mingle

23
00:02:03,671 --> 00:02:08,141
with the youth of the world
in Helsinki...

24
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:11,141
at the World Youth Conference.

25
00:02:12,150 --> 00:02:14,140
Where the democratic youth

26
00:02:15,149 --> 00:02:17,663
will meet,
sing and then go home.

27
00:02:26,147 --> 00:02:26,947
Jenõ!

28
00:02:30,667 --> 00:02:31,766
What record is that?

29
00:02:32,146 --> 00:02:34,731
Mary Lou... Got it yesterday
at the flea market.

30
00:02:35,146 --> 00:02:36,658
Wow... How much?

31
00:02:37,145 --> 00:02:39,659
For forty... Don't pull it out.

32
00:02:40,665 --> 00:02:41,654
What's it like?

33
00:02:42,145 --> 00:02:43,133
Awesome...

34
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:47,656
I haven't listened to it yet.
My dad's gramophone'd kill it.

35
00:02:50,143 --> 00:02:52,657
Now for another announcement.

36
00:02:53,663 --> 00:02:57,132
The winning lottery numbers are:

37
00:02:57,662 --> 00:03:03,657
4, 23, 28, 19...

38
00:03:07,140 --> 00:03:09,131
What? 56?

39
00:03:10,660 --> 00:03:11,648
How can that be?

40
00:03:13,139 --> 00:03:14,128
I just can't.

41
00:03:15,659 --> 00:03:19,128
The fifth number,
dear blockmates

42
00:03:19,658 --> 00:03:22,126
you can find
in Népszabadság.

43
00:03:27,657 --> 00:03:29,135
Isn't it wonderful, Aranka.

44
00:03:30,136 --> 00:03:32,650
that nothing has happened
for years.

45
00:03:33,136 --> 00:03:34,124
You're right...

46
00:03:36,135 --> 00:03:38,649
We haven't had a washing
machine for years either.

47
00:03:39,135 --> 00:03:41,125
We cry together,
we laugh together.

48
00:03:42,134 --> 00:03:45,323
We've no fanbelt, but we've got
the World Youth Conference.

49
00:03:45,653 --> 00:03:49,123
I wish it'd stay like this
for another thirty years.

50
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:53,647
Relax, it will.
You can be sure of that.

51
00:03:54,652 --> 00:03:56,131
Gotta go now...

52
00:03:57,131 --> 00:03:58,120
Do my rounds.

53
00:03:59,131 --> 00:04:00,644
Go on, dear...

54
00:04:01,131 --> 00:04:03,644
Do the rounds
of your little empire.

55
00:04:05,650 --> 00:04:07,129
I'll go back to the washroom

56
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:10,117
and destroy my lungs
with that good hot steam.

57
00:04:11,649 --> 00:04:12,449
Simon!

58
00:04:13,649 --> 00:04:14,448
The bucket.

59
00:04:16,128 --> 00:04:17,641
You forgot the bucket...

60
00:04:19,128 --> 00:04:20,640
You've got to get ice.

61
00:04:21,647 --> 00:04:22,636
Lots of it.

62
00:04:26,126 --> 00:04:29,118
Cos our quiet and well deserved
weekend is coming.

63
00:04:44,123 --> 00:04:48,638
I feel a bit low today,

64
00:04:51,122 --> 00:04:55,637
Unhappiness took over me a bit.

65
00:04:58,121 --> 00:05:00,634
I feel a bit like

66
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:04,108
A sulky little kid

67
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:10,113
Whose toy's been taken away.

68
00:05:12,118 --> 00:05:14,632
Why did they deduct 200 forints,
comrade?

69
00:05:15,118 --> 00:05:16,107
How unfair!

70
00:05:16,638 --> 00:05:19,629
They didn't give me overtime.

71
00:05:23,116 --> 00:05:27,632
I feel a bit low today,

72
00:05:30,115 --> 00:05:34,107
This lovely world got a bit cloudly.

73
00:05:36,634 --> 00:05:39,625
I've been screwed up a bit,

74
00:05:40,113 --> 00:05:43,105
but it's not the first time.

75
00:05:43,633 --> 00:05:48,626
My heart thinks of you
without anger.

76
00:05:51,631 --> 00:05:54,099
Come on, dear buddy.

77
00:05:54,631 --> 00:05:57,098
Cheer me up quick,

78
00:05:58,110 --> 00:06:02,103
See, I'm about to break down.

79
00:06:05,109 --> 00:06:07,623
Come on, dear guitar,

80
00:06:08,628 --> 00:06:11,096
I need a real song,

81
00:06:11,628 --> 00:06:16,621
To get rid of my complaints.

82
00:06:32,104 --> 00:06:36,620
I feel a bit low today,

83
00:06:39,103 --> 00:06:43,618
Unhappiness is new to me,

84
00:06:46,102 --> 00:06:48,615
I give myself a shake.

85
00:06:49,621 --> 00:06:52,089
You see, everything is fine,

86
00:06:53,101 --> 00:06:58,094
I look at you with my head high.

87
00:07:00,019 --> 00:07:01,008
Dear Attila...

88
00:07:01,539 --> 00:07:03,530
I'm sorry I haven't written before.

89
00:07:04,019 --> 00:07:06,532
We finally made it to Toronto
from Austria.

90
00:07:07,018 --> 00:07:10,010
Don't think that in two years
I've forgotten you.

91
00:07:12,017 --> 00:07:13,006
Katinka!

92
00:07:14,017 --> 00:07:17,008
She's been breathing good
Canadian air for years now.

93
00:07:18,536 --> 00:07:21,341
I wish I could breathe with you
there. And not here.

94
00:07:33,014 --> 00:07:35,213
Those who can recite poetry,
sing, dance.

95
00:07:36,013 --> 00:07:37,526
play music or do a comic act

96
00:07:38,533 --> 00:07:41,337
should register at the local
Communist Youth office.

97
00:07:41,532 --> 00:07:45,002
First prize: a trip to Helsinki,
to the World Youth Conference.

98
00:07:46,011 --> 00:07:46,811
That's it!

99
00:07:48,531 --> 00:07:50,010
Dear Katinka,

100
00:07:50,531 --> 00:07:55,001
It was in lunch break at the
factory when I made my decision.

101
00:07:56,010 --> 00:07:57,522
I can't write down what it is,

102
00:07:58,009 --> 00:08:00,924
all I can say is the air
you breathe gave me strength.

103
00:08:01,529 --> 00:08:03,893
Please give me your address.
Hugs, Attila...

104
00:08:04,528 --> 00:08:06,519
No, kisses, Attila.

105
00:08:09,007 --> 00:08:11,521
Uncle Pista!
Is Helsinki in the West?

106
00:08:12,527 --> 00:08:16,519
- West it is.
- How can you be so sure of that?

107
00:08:17,006 --> 00:08:18,519
It's more like North-West.

108
00:08:19,006 --> 00:08:20,996
East-West. It's up there.

109
00:08:22,005 --> 00:08:23,996
- Friendly.
- Semi-friendly.

110
00:08:24,525 --> 00:08:26,992
Helsinki's in the North.

111
00:08:33,523 --> 00:08:35,991
Why aren't you
in the factory canteen?

112
00:08:37,002 --> 00:08:38,515
It's pancakes.

113
00:08:40,002 --> 00:08:41,515
Haven't got a ticket.

114
00:08:42,002 --> 00:08:43,514
Do you like pancakes?

115
00:08:44,521 --> 00:08:46,989
Come on. I understand you.

116
00:08:48,001 --> 00:08:49,991
I see you got touched
by politics.

117
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:53,514
Helsinki, right?

118
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:57,511
Well, right now... it's the West,

119
00:08:58,519 --> 00:09:01,510
but there's a ferry
over to Leningrad.

120
00:09:02,518 --> 00:09:03,997
No thanks then...

121
00:09:04,518 --> 00:09:07,509
Today Attila Bánki,
semi-skilled worker,

122
00:09:07,997 --> 00:09:10,989
asked whether Helsinki
was in the West.

123
00:09:11,996 --> 00:09:14,510
The workers argued over this
at length

124
00:09:15,516 --> 00:09:18,507
meanwhile István Furman,
shop steward,

125
00:09:19,515 --> 00:09:25,510
put the bucket used for stubs
on worker Sándor Gáspár's head.

126
00:09:26,474 --> 00:09:30,989
The ensuing curses did not infer
incitement against the state.

127
00:09:31,993 --> 00:09:33,984
Ibolya, 4/4 subdivision,
Screw Factory.

128
00:09:34,472 --> 00:09:35,985
Date: two shots of moonshine.

129
00:09:37,472 --> 00:09:39,891
It says here the winners
will go to Helsinki.

130
00:09:40,471 --> 00:09:41,460
You get it?

131
00:09:41,991 --> 00:09:44,459
World Youth Conference.

132
00:09:45,470 --> 00:09:48,462
Some kind of huge Communist
Youth Meeting, right?

133
00:09:48,990 --> 00:09:50,981
Who cares?
Helsinki in the West.

134
00:09:51,989 --> 00:09:53,419
We get there and walk off.

135
00:09:53,989 --> 00:09:56,319
Screw their three years
of military service.

136
00:09:56,469 --> 00:09:57,457
You sure?

137
00:09:57,988 --> 00:09:59,467
It's in the paper.

138
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:06,980
What are we good at?

139
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:09,457
Nothing at all.

140
00:10:09,986 --> 00:10:10,975
Pop group!

141
00:10:11,466 --> 00:10:13,980
I feel a bit low today,

142
00:10:15,465 --> 00:10:17,979
Unhappiness is new to me,

143
00:10:18,985 --> 00:10:21,976
I shake myself a bit
You see, everything is fine

144
00:10:22,464 --> 00:10:24,455
I look at you with my head high.

145
00:10:28,983 --> 00:10:31,897
- What are we going to play?
- I'll go get some music.

146
00:10:32,462 --> 00:10:34,976
Let's pick up some chicks...

147
00:10:36,462 --> 00:10:37,974
We'll meet at the lake cafe...

148
00:10:38,981 --> 00:10:40,460
- Let's tell him too.
- Jenci!

149
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:44,449
Have you heard?

150
00:10:45,980 --> 00:10:47,685
- World Youth Conference.
- WYC.

151
00:10:48,979 --> 00:10:50,458
Who? Stop a minute.

152
00:10:51,459 --> 00:10:52,972
You've got something there.

153
00:10:53,979 --> 00:10:55,457
What's in the bag?

154
00:10:58,978 --> 00:11:00,968
Thank you...

155
00:11:02,977 --> 00:11:04,968
Uncle Pista...

156
00:11:06,456 --> 00:11:08,970
Live happily ever after,

157
00:11:09,976 --> 00:11:11,454
with my blessing.

158
00:11:12,455 --> 00:11:17,448
He may stand all the rows.

159
00:11:18,974 --> 00:11:20,965
I'm leaving.

160
00:11:21,974 --> 00:11:23,964
I get off light,

161
00:11:24,973 --> 00:11:27,441
However hard I try,

162
00:11:27,973 --> 00:11:29,451
I'm not down.

163
00:11:30,972 --> 00:11:33,440
Now I'm finally free

164
00:11:33,972 --> 00:11:36,439
I'll live with no worries

165
00:11:37,451 --> 00:11:41,443
My surly baby
won't boss me around

166
00:11:42,450 --> 00:11:45,442
I suffered quite enough

167
00:11:46,449 --> 00:11:48,963
From tomorrow I'll laugh too

168
00:11:49,449 --> 00:11:52,963
Like all others,
it's better that way.

169
00:11:54,448 --> 00:11:58,440
Live happily for a hundred years

170
00:11:58,967 --> 00:12:00,958
You have my blessing

171
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:06,960
He may stand all the rows.

172
00:12:07,966 --> 00:12:10,433
I'm leaving.

173
00:12:11,445 --> 00:12:13,436
I get off light,

174
00:12:13,965 --> 00:12:16,432
However hard I try,

175
00:12:16,964 --> 00:12:19,955
I'm not down.

176
00:12:23,963 --> 00:12:24,952
It's Saturday...

177
00:12:34,441 --> 00:12:35,430
You cad!

178
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:44,953
- Hi, I'm Etelka.
- I'm Olga.

179
00:12:45,439 --> 00:12:47,199
- Shall we have a Bambi?
- Great.

180
00:12:48,439 --> 00:12:50,952
- Two Bambis, please, with a straw.
- Right away.

181
00:12:51,958 --> 00:12:53,949
What do you think?
A little romance?

182
00:12:54,957 --> 00:12:56,436
Maybe. Relax.

183
00:12:56,957 --> 00:12:58,772
Play it cool... That's the point.

184
00:12:59,437 --> 00:13:00,425
Summer's so good...

185
00:13:01,956 --> 00:13:04,948
- Everything's full of love.
- And disappointment.

186
00:13:05,436 --> 00:13:08,405
- Mine's the ponytail, yours is
the beehive. - No away.

187
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:11,422
- Then you say hello.
- The ponytail is yours.

188
00:13:13,994 --> 00:13:19,431
Watch it... Play it cool.

189
00:13:27,952 --> 00:13:29,464
I don't think we've met.

190
00:13:29,951 --> 00:13:32,321
- I don't meet people this way.
- Me neither.

191
00:13:32,471 --> 00:13:33,950
Kuno Purábl, at your service.

192
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:37,942
I got goosebumps already.
I'm going to be a ballerina.

193
00:13:39,470 --> 00:13:41,229
I can only contemplate marriage.

194
00:13:42,469 --> 00:13:44,834
Can I show you
my most treasured possession?

195
00:13:45,469 --> 00:13:47,943
- No. - Your wish is my command.
- What is it?

196
00:13:48,468 --> 00:13:50,173
Have you seen anything like it?

197
00:13:50,948 --> 00:13:53,367
What's the velvet for?
Is it expensive stuff?

198
00:13:53,947 --> 00:13:55,938
- Priceless.
- Is it from abroad?

199
00:13:56,467 --> 00:13:57,945
May I take it out?

200
00:13:58,946 --> 00:14:00,459
Do you know what it is?

201
00:14:04,945 --> 00:14:05,745
Pig!

202
00:14:09,464 --> 00:14:10,943
I beg your pardon.

203
00:14:15,943 --> 00:14:16,932
What was it?

204
00:14:21,942 --> 00:14:24,934
Gosh... and I almost touched it.

205
00:14:27,461 --> 00:14:29,929
Those were MIGs
and I didn't even see them.

206
00:14:32,460 --> 00:14:33,939
They're American cigarettes.

207
00:14:36,460 --> 00:14:37,938
Look... American cigarettes.

208
00:14:40,939 --> 00:14:42,929
Damn, it's a Chesterfield.

209
00:14:46,938 --> 00:14:47,927
How masculine.

210
00:14:48,937 --> 00:14:50,928
They say there's cocaine in them.

211
00:14:51,457 --> 00:14:54,926
Coca-cola has opium and
sex is porn, my dad said.

212
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:56,925
Manci's here!

213
00:15:01,455 --> 00:15:03,923
- She's cheating on me.
- You two going out?

214
00:15:04,455 --> 00:15:06,445
What can you see, Mr. Bajkon?

215
00:15:07,934 --> 00:15:09,447
Manci, you tricked me.

216
00:15:10,454 --> 00:15:13,303
Could you tell Angéla
she can look into my telescope?

217
00:15:13,453 --> 00:15:15,444
Can I take a look too?

218
00:15:15,933 --> 00:15:17,445
Of course. Even at home.

219
00:15:17,932 --> 00:15:20,924
After all you only live
ten paces away from me.

220
00:15:21,452 --> 00:15:25,444
But my dream is that
she will take a peak one day.

221
00:15:26,451 --> 00:15:29,442
Angéla! Will you look
into Mr. Bajkon's telescope?

222
00:15:30,450 --> 00:15:32,918
I'm not in the mood,
how about later?

223
00:15:33,450 --> 00:15:34,928
Alright... When exactly?

224
00:15:35,449 --> 00:15:36,928
Hi... The music.

225
00:15:40,448 --> 00:15:41,713
So? Did you discuss it?

226
00:15:42,448 --> 00:15:44,439
- I'm in.
- Who will sing?

227
00:15:45,927 --> 00:15:46,916
Attila.

228
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:50,439
- Why him?
- He's dying to meet his girlfriend.

229
00:15:51,447 --> 00:15:53,921
- I want to get out of here too.
- Don't yell.

230
00:15:54,446 --> 00:15:56,296
The singer always gets
the best chicks.

231
00:15:56,446 --> 00:15:59,295
- So three guitars and the drums.
- I play the guitar.

232
00:15:59,445 --> 00:16:00,775
- Me too.
- We need a drummer.

233
00:16:00,925 --> 00:16:02,915
Guys, if we pull this off

234
00:16:03,444 --> 00:16:07,437
I'm off to Brazil
to eat bananas

235
00:16:08,444 --> 00:16:09,432
non-stop.

236
00:17:09,353 --> 00:17:12,822
Mr. Bajkon... Mr. Bajkon...

237
00:17:16,352 --> 00:17:17,830
Here's your chance to cut in

238
00:17:18,351 --> 00:17:19,830
and dance with Angéla.

239
00:17:20,351 --> 00:17:22,342
Cut in, out? Look, Manci,

240
00:17:22,831 --> 00:17:26,345
my affection isn't
a rollercoaster.

241
00:17:39,988 --> 00:17:41,087
Son, are you hungry?

242
00:17:41,987 --> 00:17:43,978
Bananas... I want bananas, Ma.

243
00:17:44,987 --> 00:17:46,801
Where the hell can I get bananas?

244
00:17:46,986 --> 00:17:48,977
Your hair's long.
Get it cut tomorrow.

245
00:18:01,544 --> 00:18:03,056
I count to three...

246
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:05,383
Three!

247
00:18:05,543 --> 00:18:07,534
Good day, blockmates.

248
00:18:08,063 --> 00:18:12,533
I see the Flying Day is going well.

249
00:18:13,062 --> 00:18:13,912
But it's not over yet.

250
00:18:14,062 --> 00:18:25,050
- Could we be on familiar terms?
- Who do you think you are?

251
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,909
Just because I danced with you,
you can molest me?

252
00:18:28,059 --> 00:18:30,573
But I only touched
your knee bone.

253
00:18:31,059 --> 00:18:34,050
Jesus Christ!
What are you? A butcher?

254
00:18:35,058 --> 00:18:36,047
I just...

255
00:18:36,578 --> 00:18:38,777
- You just handle the paddles.
- Will do.

256
00:18:39,057 --> 00:18:41,571
- What are you doing?
- We've cleaving the waves.

257
00:18:42,057 --> 00:18:45,571
Full tilt. What's the water like?
Would you like to have a splash?

258
00:18:46,056 --> 00:18:48,570
Come on, exert yourself,
once you've invited me.

259
00:18:55,494 --> 00:18:56,973
Just a moment.

260
00:18:59,494 --> 00:19:00,482
What is it?

261
00:19:01,493 --> 00:19:02,972
