I got sleepy...

1061
01:11:52,339 --> 01:11:53,818
and now we're sleeping.

1062
01:11:54,338 --> 01:11:55,817
We got through?

1063
01:11:56,818 --> 01:11:58,331
I thought I dreamt it.

1064
01:12:03,337 --> 01:12:04,326
My father!

1065
01:12:08,816 --> 01:12:10,329
Good evening...

1066
01:12:17,334 --> 01:12:18,323
The thing is...

1067
01:12:20,334 --> 01:12:21,134
Angela,

1068
01:12:22,334 --> 01:12:28,329
love has caught up with you.

1069
01:12:30,332 --> 01:12:33,802
Angela, Angela,

1070
01:12:35,331 --> 01:12:38,801
I get dizzy all over

1071
01:12:40,810 --> 01:12:44,803
And the shadows turn into light

1072
01:12:45,809 --> 01:12:49,324
As I see you in my arms.

1073
01:12:51,329 --> 01:12:54,320
Angela,

1074
01:12:56,328 --> 01:12:59,797
My little angel.

1075
01:13:03,806 --> 01:13:04,795
What are you doing?

1076
01:13:06,806 --> 01:13:08,016
Who is this young man?

1077
01:13:08,805 --> 01:13:11,797
- Who are you?
- He's got no place to stay...

1078
01:13:12,805 --> 01:13:13,794
What's going on?

1079
01:13:14,804 --> 01:13:17,609
A girl's greatest asset
is her virginity these days.

1080
01:13:17,804 --> 01:13:20,004
And you're messing around
with a stranger

1081
01:13:20,803 --> 01:13:22,794
along with my mandrel
and my hand-drill.

1082
01:13:23,323 --> 01:13:25,790
What if the plane I got
from grandpa disappears?

1083
01:13:27,322 --> 01:13:28,801
- Greetings...
- Mom!

1084
01:14:21,873 --> 01:14:23,863
God, you've got cool parents.

1085
01:14:27,872 --> 01:14:30,863
I don't want to see you here
in ten minutes.

1086
01:14:35,870 --> 01:14:37,349
Give me a good coffee.

1087
01:14:40,349 --> 01:14:41,862
Give me something to drink.

1088
01:14:43,869 --> 01:14:45,354
What are you so glum about?

1089
01:14:45,868 --> 01:14:47,347
You're the talk of the block.

1090
01:14:47,868 --> 01:14:49,859
The egg-beaters.

1091
01:14:50,348 --> 01:14:52,861
The egg-beaters complicated
our qualifying.

1092
01:14:53,867 --> 01:14:54,856
I don't get it.

1093
01:14:55,347 --> 01:14:58,338
Felix says we qualified
because of the egg-beaters.

1094
01:14:58,866 --> 01:15:02,336
- They judged it as a comedy turn.
- See what you did?

1095
01:15:03,345 --> 01:15:05,336
Women overcomplicate things.

1096
01:15:06,345 --> 01:15:09,699
Don't be crazy... You're in the
finals and that's what counts.

1097
01:15:09,864 --> 01:15:12,332
Yes, we qualified
and we're going to Helsinki.

1098
01:15:13,864 --> 01:15:16,331
How'll we get there?
Plane? Train? Bus?

1099
01:15:17,343 --> 01:15:18,856
IBUSZ!

1100
01:15:19,863 --> 01:15:21,853
No, with a trolleybus.

1101
01:15:22,862 --> 01:15:24,853
You got a letter, Attila.

1102
01:15:25,862 --> 01:15:26,661
What?

1103
01:15:33,340 --> 01:15:34,853
Dear Attila!

1104
01:15:35,340 --> 01:15:37,853
I'm standing here
at Niagara Falls

1105
01:15:38,339 --> 01:15:40,330
watching the water falling

1106
01:15:40,859 --> 01:15:42,850
and imagining you here with me.

1107
01:15:43,858 --> 01:15:46,850
You're drinking Coca-Cola,
I have a Pepsi and we enjoy...

1108
01:15:47,858 --> 01:15:49,336
Katinka... I'm coming!

1109
01:15:50,857 --> 01:15:51,846
For sure.

1110
01:15:53,337 --> 01:15:54,326
You coming, Attila?

1111
01:15:55,856 --> 01:15:58,324
Too bad she doesn't speak
Hungarian. Look...

1112
01:15:58,856 --> 01:16:00,334
The other is Mastroianni.

1113
01:16:02,335 --> 01:16:04,849
- A pretzel, please.
- Who was that?

1114
01:16:05,335 --> 01:16:06,847
These people do live!

1115
01:16:07,334 --> 01:16:08,847
What a woman!

1116
01:16:09,334 --> 01:16:10,847
Just imagine!

1117
01:16:11,334 --> 01:16:13,324
And here we have
construction camps.

1118
01:16:13,853 --> 01:16:16,321
- And semolina noodles.
- And cheap black drawers.

1119
01:16:16,853 --> 01:16:18,331
She looks like Manci.

1120
01:16:20,332 --> 01:16:22,846
- Damn this life!
- Damn this Dolce Vita!

1121
01:16:24,851 --> 01:16:26,330
I don't want to rot here.

1122
01:16:26,851 --> 01:16:28,330
Hush! Rot someplace else.

1123
01:16:29,330 --> 01:16:30,130
Damn...

1124
01:16:31,330 --> 01:16:32,319
Pretzel, please.

1125
01:16:32,850 --> 01:16:35,317
Who was it? Don't mess with me.

1126
01:16:35,849 --> 01:16:39,842
I know you're all here
to watch that Swedish cow!

1127
01:16:41,328 --> 01:16:42,317
Pretzel. Quick.

1128
01:16:44,848 --> 01:16:46,662
Who was it?
I'll call a policeman.

1129
01:16:47,327 --> 01:16:48,316
Aren't you one?

1130
01:16:50,327 --> 01:16:51,839
Dolce Vita...

1131
01:16:52,326 --> 01:16:53,315
Dodi...

1132
01:17:06,324 --> 01:17:09,838
- Anita, come here or I'll come
to you. - That's right, let's go.

1133
01:17:11,323 --> 01:17:12,836
We'll stop the screening.

1134
01:17:13,323 --> 01:17:14,835
Quick. They'll stop it.

1135
01:17:19,842 --> 01:17:20,941
Anita, I'm coming...

1136
01:17:24,841 --> 01:17:25,830
What a riot!

1137
01:17:27,840 --> 01:17:30,308
We have to play at the finals.
Don't get caught.

1138
01:17:30,840 --> 01:17:32,318
We can't miss this!

1139
01:17:35,839 --> 01:17:37,829
Shu-shu madness,

1140
01:17:38,838 --> 01:17:40,317
the danger is here.

1141
01:18:45,347 --> 01:18:46,859
What's going on here?

1142
01:18:47,346 --> 01:18:48,859
Don't you recognize me?

1143
01:18:50,346 --> 01:18:53,860
Why are you here
at this hour, Jenõ?

1144
01:18:54,345 --> 01:18:55,334
That's him.

1145
01:18:56,345 --> 01:18:57,334
Jenõ, is that you?

1146
01:18:58,864 --> 01:18:59,853
Let me see you.

1147
01:19:00,864 --> 01:19:02,343
You don't remember me.

1148
01:19:03,343 --> 01:19:05,334
Give a kiss to your auntie.
Come on!

1149
01:19:05,863 --> 01:19:08,331
Didn't your father
tell you about me?

1150
01:19:09,342 --> 01:19:12,334
What are doing here?
It's midnight.

1151
01:19:12,862 --> 01:19:14,341
Did you break in?

1152
01:19:14,861 --> 01:19:16,340
We're rehearsing.

1153
01:19:17,341 --> 01:19:20,855
Preparing for the
Talent Contest.

1154
01:19:21,340 --> 01:19:22,329
Talent Contest?

1155
01:19:23,340 --> 01:19:24,329
I heard about it.

1156
01:19:24,860 --> 01:19:26,338
You're so cute.

1157
01:19:28,859 --> 01:19:30,014
Where's the restroom?

1158
01:19:30,339 --> 01:19:31,328
That way...

1159
01:19:31,858 --> 01:19:32,847
I'll be right back.

1160
01:19:33,858 --> 01:19:35,337
Don't start without me.

1161
01:19:39,857 --> 01:19:41,336
Is your auntie a cop?

1162
01:19:42,337 --> 01:19:44,850
Idiots, I don't even know
who she is.

1163
01:19:46,856 --> 01:19:48,847
How's it going?

1164
01:19:49,855 --> 01:19:52,323
We were at the movies.
Come on home now.

1165
01:19:52,855 --> 01:19:54,845
- Are you hungry?
- I want a banana.

1166
01:19:55,334 --> 01:19:57,325
You're not a monkey.

1167
01:19:57,854 --> 01:20:00,845
Hunger? I can tell
you were never on the stage.

1168
01:20:01,853 --> 01:20:04,163
An artist never feels hunger
in rehearsals.

1169
01:20:05,333 --> 01:20:06,652
What are you staring at?

1170
01:20:09,332 --> 01:20:12,323
Ernesztin, from Tömõ Street!
Is that you?

1171
01:20:12,851 --> 01:20:15,319
Aranka Varga,
the baker's daughter...

1172
01:20:16,331 --> 01:20:18,844
Where we went for ice-cream,
right, Simon?

1173
01:20:19,330 --> 01:20:22,845
Jenõ, go home. The rest go to
the barber. The rehearsal's over.

1174
01:20:26,849 --> 01:20:29,316
- Greetings!
- Goodnight.

1175
01:20:31,328 --> 01:20:34,133
What a coincidence that
you're on duty in this area.

1176
01:20:34,847 --> 01:20:37,315
Public safety throws me
here and there.

1177
01:20:37,847 --> 01:20:40,315
But I see you guard
the family nest.

1178
01:20:40,846 --> 01:20:42,837
Jenõ's in the Talent Contest.

1179
01:20:43,846 --> 01:20:46,313
We agreed that
she'd get out of your life

1180
01:20:46,845 --> 01:20:49,925
and I'd overlook your little
affair in return, whereas...

1181
01:20:50,325 --> 01:20:52,838
Surely we're not going to
make a drama out of this?

1182
01:20:53,324 --> 01:20:55,315
Let's get a shot of
coffee liqueur.

1183
01:20:56,324 --> 01:20:57,424
Béla, where are you?

1184
01:20:58,323 --> 01:20:59,836
Let's drink!

1185
01:21:00,843 --> 01:21:02,108
What movie did you see?

1186
01:21:02,843 --> 01:21:04,321
La Dolce Vita.

1187
01:21:06,322 --> 01:21:07,122
Dreadful.

1188
01:21:07,322 --> 01:21:11,314
Since it's been on
things have got out of routine.

1189
01:21:11,841 --> 01:21:15,310
The whole city's gone mad.
I'd ban it.

1190
01:21:16,320 --> 01:21:18,311
To our health then!

1191
01:21:20,839 --> 01:21:22,830
Wander through the night with me

1192
01:21:23,839 --> 01:21:25,830
Pest is worth an evening

1193
01:21:26,838 --> 01:21:28,829
Every window winks at us

1194
01:21:29,838 --> 01:21:31,829
Pest is worth an evening.

1195
01:21:32,837 --> 01:21:35,305
We walk Buda's cobbled streets

1196
01:21:35,837 --> 01:21:38,304
Beside the island, by the bridges

1197
01:21:39,316 --> 01:21:41,307
A hundred moonrays on the Danube

1198
01:21:42,316 --> 01:21:44,829
Starshine plus me.

1199
01:21:45,835 --> 01:21:47,826
And if this is not enough

1200
01:21:48,835 --> 01:21:50,313
It's just the beginning

1201
01:21:51,834 --> 01:21:53,825
You'll see after the first kiss

1202
01:21:54,833 --> 01:21:56,824
That Pest is worth an evening

1203
01:21:57,833 --> 01:22:00,824
Pest is worth an evening.

1204
01:22:18,789 --> 01:22:20,439
Did you bring the egg-beaters?

1205
01:22:22,269 --> 01:22:24,782
Are you nuts? I'm a drummer
not a pastry-cook.

1206
01:22:27,788 --> 01:22:29,602
Ede didn't bring the egg-beaters.

1207
01:22:30,267 --> 01:22:31,862
We can send someone for them.

1208
01:22:32,787 --> 01:22:34,437
You want to make a fool of me?

1209
01:22:34,787 --> 01:22:36,777
Not a fool, a winner.

1210
01:22:39,266 --> 01:22:40,778
Let me through...

1211
01:22:42,265 --> 01:22:43,254
Boys,

1212
01:22:44,265 --> 01:22:46,255
have you seen Margit from II/c?

1213
01:22:46,784 --> 01:22:47,884
They didn't qualify.

1214
01:22:48,784 --> 01:22:51,114
I don't need the guy in chains,
only the girl.

1215
01:22:51,264 --> 01:22:54,618
If you see her tell her to come
to the basement dressing room.

1216
01:22:58,262 --> 01:23:00,253
- Contestant?
- No, just audience.

1217
01:23:01,262 --> 01:23:02,857
My friend will recite a poem.

1218
01:23:03,262 --> 01:23:06,253
- Come with me to the basement.
- But I didn't do anything.

1219
01:23:06,781 --> 01:23:08,260
I can see that. Now you will.

1220
01:23:09,260 --> 01:23:11,251
It's in the block interest.
Come on.

1221
01:23:11,780 --> 01:23:13,771
Help! It's not the 1950s!

1222
01:23:14,260 --> 01:23:16,184
You're right, it's the 60s.
Come on.

1223
01:23:16,779 --> 01:23:18,629
- What about my friend?
- Go inside.

1224
01:23:18,779 --> 01:23:19,579
Dodi!

1225
01:23:20,778 --> 01:23:23,246
I couldn't sleep all night
I was so nervous.

1226
01:23:23,778 --> 01:23:26,769
I know, I was there too.
Don't you remember?

1227
01:23:28,777 --> 01:23:29,766
Hi, Attila.

1228
01:23:30,777 --> 01:23:34,246
We came to root for you,
though I prefer Bach.

1229
01:23:35,776 --> 01:23:37,414
I didn't know you were dating.

1230
01:23:37,895 --> 01:23:40,409
I didn't want him behind me
all the time.

1231
01:23:40,895 --> 01:23:43,409
- I have to talk to you.
- Angela...

1232
01:23:45,894 --> 01:23:46,694
What is it?

1233
01:23:47,894 --> 01:23:49,406
I must tell you something.

1234
01:23:50,413 --> 01:23:52,404
Who knows,
you might win the finals.

1235
01:23:53,413 --> 01:23:55,403
Might? We will.

1236
01:23:55,892 --> 01:23:58,884
If you do, then first I have
to admit

1237
01:23:59,892 --> 01:24:01,596
that I wrote Katinka's letters.

1238
01:24:02,411 --> 01:24:03,890
What? Katinka's letters...

1239
01:24:04,891 --> 01:24:08,405
I wrote them all. Even the first
one four years ago.

1240
01:24:09,890 --> 01:24:11,403
You're making it up.

1241
01:24:12,889 --> 01:24:16,404
We drink Coca-Cola,
and the Niagara Falls...

1242
01:24:18,408 --> 01:24:19,397
What is all this?

1243
01:24:21,408 --> 01:24:22,397
Shu-shu madness.

1244
01:24:23,408 --> 01:24:24,396
Manci!

1245
01:24:26,407 --> 01:24:28,875
- You're an idiot.
- I'll defect anyway.

1246
01:24:32,406 --> 01:24:33,395
Manci's back.

1247
01:24:34,406 --> 01:24:35,205
How are you?

1248
01:24:35,885 --> 01:24:36,874
I'm at the TV.

1249
01:24:37,405 --> 01:24:40,874
I'm reserve announcer for the
Czech Experimental Program.

1250
01:24:41,404 --> 01:24:43,872
I'm on unpaid leave
so I came home.

1251
01:24:44,404 --> 01:24:45,393
Manci!

1252
01:24:45,884 --> 01:24:48,875
Could you put my suitcase
in the cloakroom?

1253
01:24:49,403 --> 01:24:50,392
I'd be happy to.

1254
01:24:52,882 --> 01:24:53,871
Dear Angela...

1255
01:24:55,882 --> 01:24:56,997
- Margit?
- What is it?

1256
01:24:57,522 --> 01:24:59,989
Uncle Simon is looking for you.

1257
01:25:02,521 --> 01:25:05,512
Margit! Thank God you're here.
Stand there.

1258
01:25:09,000 --> 01:25:09,799
Ladies!

1259
01:25:10,519 --> 01:25:12,987
One of the women's choir is sick.

1260
01:25:13,999 --> 01:25:16,512
They're sure winners
in their class

1261
01:25:16,998 --> 01:25:18,511
so they'd go to the WYC.

1262
01:25:19,998 --> 01:25:22,802
- What are you doing here?
- Me? I came with Margit.

1263
01:25:22,997 --> 01:25:24,510
You should be with your band.

1264
01:25:24,997 --> 01:25:27,988
Go on, tune, sing and
go to the barber. Get going!

1265
01:25:52,792 --> 01:25:55,259
Could you close it,
there's such a draught.

1266
01:25:56,791 --> 01:25:57,780
Which are you?

1267
01:25:58,791 --> 01:26:00,270
It said... on the door...

1268
01:26:01,270 --> 01:26:02,370
We're the pop group.

1269
01:26:03,270 --> 01:26:04,783
You're going to Helsinki, no?

1270
01:26:05,790 --> 01:26:09,259
Then you must be
from Bánki Dixieland.

1271
01:26:11,269 --> 01:26:12,257
Let's see.

1272
01:26:13,788 --> 01:26:15,267
What are these outfits?

1273
01:26:16,788 --> 01:26:18,266
They belong to the winners.

1274
01:26:18,787 --> 01:26:20,266
The Hungarian delegation.

1275
01:26:21,267 --> 01:26:24,258
But... the finals are
only just starting.

1276
01:26:25,266 --> 01:26:27,780
Don't annoy me... They took your
measurements...

1277
01:26:28,786 --> 01:26:31,253
and didn't tell you you're going
to Helsinki?

1278
01:26:32,265 --> 01:26:34,256
The girl who can wear these boots

1279
01:26:34,785 --> 01:26:36,263
will join the choir.

1280
01:26:37,264 --> 01:26:38,064
Let's start.

1281
01:26:47,262 --> 01:26:48,062
Push...

1282
01:26:52,261 --> 01:26:55,776
- Small... it won't fit.
- Push harder.

1283
01:26:56,261 --> 01:26:58,774
How can someone
have such pig feet?

1284
01:27:01,260 --> 01:27:03,251
I see it won't work.
Next please.

1285
01:27:11,778 --> 01:27:12,767
It's perfect.

1286
01:27:13,778 --> 01:27:15,256
Show me. Let me see.

1287
01:27:15,777 --> 01:27:16,766
They're too big!

1288
01:27:17,777 --> 01:27:21,461
- I'll stuff them with cotton wool.
- I'll tell you what to stuff...

1289
01:27:21,776 --> 01:27:22,576
Go on.

1290
01:27:23,776 --> 01:27:26,244
- Come on Margit.
- I don't want to.

1291
01:27:27,255 --> 01:27:28,355
Oh, come on, Margit.

1292
01:27:29,255 --> 01:27:32,246
Do you want to ruin me?
You can go to the West!

1293
01:27:32,774 --> 01:27:35,766
This is more than block interest.
Put them on!

1294
01:27:43,253 --> 01:27:44,241
We made it.

1295
01:27:51,771 --> 01:27:53,762
The rival group is starting now.

1296
01:27:54,251 --> 01:27:55,763
Then it's us.

1297
01:27:58,250 --> 01:28:00,241
We should discuss what to play.

1298
01:28:12,807 --> 01:28:14,798
Dolly-bird smile at me

1299
01:28:15,807 --> 01:28:17,798
Dolly-bird fall for me

1300
01:28:18,806 --> 01:28:20,797
You will be my sweet angel

1301
01:28:21,806 --> 01:28:24,273
Guardian angel in my life's heaven

1302
01:28:25,285 --> 01:28:27,276
Dolly-bird I spoil you

1303
01:28:28,285 --> 01:28:30,798
Dolly-bird do be mine

1304
01:28:31,804 --> 01:28:33,795
Please forgive me for I

1305
01:28:34,284 --> 01:28:36,797
Die to have a kiss from you.

1306
01:29:03,519 --> 01:29:06,032
Your colourful cotton dress

1307
01:29:06,518 --> 01:29:09,032
is all flowers

1308
01:29:10,037 --> 01:29:12,028
Your gentle voice is hard to resist

1309
01:29:13,037 --> 01:29:15,028
You're a Pest girl and that's it.

1310
01:29:52,950 --> 01:29:54,941
Damn!
They cheated me.

1311
01:30:08,587 --> 01:30:10,578
I like the colour of your eyes

1312
01:30:11,587 --> 01:30:14,054
But I still don't know your name

1313
01:30:15,066 --> 01:30:18,057
Dolly-bird I love you so
I call you so

1314
01:30:19,065 --> 01:30:24,058
Dolly-bird, please be mine!

1315
01:30:26,584 --> 01:30:28,784
- Let's not play "Dolly-bird".
